This paper deals with clustering, which is a common topic in machine learning and data science. The use of decision trees to improve interpretability suggests a focus on explainable AI, which falls under the cs.AI sub-category. The theoretical analysis of clustering algorithms suggests a focus on algorithms and complexity, which falls under the cs.DS and cs.DM sub-categories. Finally, the use of clustering for geometric data suggests a focus on machine learning and pattern recognition, which falls under the cs.LG and cs.SI sub-categories.
